## 1. Verdict

The earlier designs repeatedly turned a sensible first-release subset into an
artificial research ceiling.  That drafting pattern is now superseded.

From this revision onward:

```text
release target = minimum certified regression floor
runtime refusal = current evidence boundary
nonclaim        = current theorem boundary
blocked item    = named missing proof, authority, implementation, or certificate

None of those means:
  do not investigate
  do not derive
  do not implement
  do not certify
  do not promote a stronger exact result
```

Every campaign must actively inspect adjacent exact capabilities.  A capability
supported by repository authority or a new proof is to be derived, implemented,
tested, certified, and promoted even if it was not listed in the initial release
floor.  `Not in the handoff` is not an admissible blocker.

This revision changes research authority and workflow.  It does not pretend
that an open theorem has thereby been proved.

