## 4. Artificial restrictions to revisit and lift

Status terms:

```text
TEXT LIFTED
  The handoff wording has been corrected.

ACTIVE REVISIT
  Mathematical or implementation work is still required before runtime or
  theorem promotion.

CURRENT GUARD
  The runtime/nonclaim boundary remains until that work is certified.

RETAIN
  This was not artificial; it protects mathematical validity or evidence.

REFUTED
  The proposed expansion is false at the stated scope; retain the exact
  obstruction and investigate only a properly reduced or altered target.
```

### AR-01 — Treating the named release as the whole campaign

**Old restriction:** completing the enumerated stage checklist ended research
even when adjacent exact extensions were visible.  
**Replacement:** every checklist is a minimum regression floor followed by a
mandatory expansion-discovery and promotion pass.  
**Status:** `TEXT LIFTED`; apply this pattern to every future handoff.

### AR-02 — Exactly two DBP corridors

**Old restriction:** only `ell_up` and `ell_down` could be admitted, and further
routes were outside campaign scope.  
**Replacement:** retain those two as certified seeds while admitting any exact
custom route whose sheet, isotopy/free-group data, divisor clearance, class
action, hostile tests, and nested certificate replay close.  
**Status:** `TEXT LIFTED`; `ACTIVE REVISIT` for route families not already
promoted.

### AR-03 — No route identity, composition, or reversal algebra

**Old restriction:** general composition/reversal was labelled out of scope
rather than an immediate generalization target.  
**Replacement:** derive identity, concatenation, inverse/reversal, endpoint
typing, digest composition, and class-action functoriality exactly.  
**Status:** `TEXT LIFTED`; `ACTIVE REVISIT` outside capabilities already closed
in later live work.

### AR-04 — No custom homotopy classes or full-plane exact paths

**Old restriction:** the handoffs confined the engine to two fixed polygonal
representatives in the initial shear domain.  
**Replacement:** promote further exact path and homotopy classes domain by
