## 5. Restrictions that are justified and must remain

The following are not artificial scope locks:

| ID | Protected invariant | Reason retained |
|---|---|---|
| PI-01 | No theorem claim before an exact proof or authoritative source exists | Prevents scope enthusiasm from becoming false mathematics. |
| PI-02 | Typed runtime refusal until a capability is promoted | Prevents unsupported requests from returning fabricated success. |
| PI-03 | Exact arithmetic and certified bounds where the theorem is exact | Floating sampling cannot prove divisor clearance, topology, or integrality. |
| PI-04 | Source, schema, implementation, request, plan, and certificate binding | Makes replay and provenance meaningful. |
| PI-05 | Explicit sheet, orientation, route word/isotopy, boundary, and ring typing | Labels and endpoints alone do not determine the transported class. |
| PI-06 | No silent zero for unknown compact corrections | Zero is a mathematical assertion, not a placeholder. |
| PI-07 | No absolute scalar from quotient-only data | An exact representative and evaluation map are genuinely required. |
| PI-08 | The proved boundary obstruction to replacing `i` by an integral class at the stated curve/native lattices | This is a theorem at its declared scope; expansion may seek other coefficient categories or carriers but may not erase it. |
| PI-09 | Do not infer full-surface claims from native-image injectivity or `(1/4)R_Z` | Rational left inversion on the native image is not integral whole-surface primitivity. |
| PI-10 | Preserve legacy certificate locks and unrelated dirty-worktree changes | Expansion must not destroy already certified behavior or user work. |
| PI-11 | No production use of stale scout code | The live typed implementation and its source closure are the operative object. |
| PI-12 | Independent third realization must satisfy a real independence criterion | A reparameterization, quotient, or isogeny is not independent merely because it has a new label. |

These invariants constrain how an expansion is proved and released.  They do not
constrain which mathematically meaningful expansion may be attempted.

