## 6. Promotion protocol

An artificial restriction is fully lifted in production only when the proposed
extension supplies:

```text
1. authority
   canonical theorem source or a new exact proof

2. domain
   exact carrier, coefficient category, singular/wall exclusions, and boundary

3. semantics
   immutable typed state and explicit operation

4. laws
   identity/composition/inverse, naturality, pairing, boundary, or other laws
   appropriate to the object

5. exact implementation
   no fixture-based success and no hidden numerical theorem substitution

6. hostile tests
   wrong route, sheet, sign, ring, boundary, digest, wall, and scope escalation

7. certificate and verifier
   deterministic clean-process generation and independent replay

8. compatibility
   frozen locks and unrelated user changes preserved

9. publication
   stage report, gap-ledger update, and theorem/ensemble insertion where the
   mathematical claim changed
```

Failure of one item blocks only that extension and its dependants.  It does not
restore the old global scope ceiling.

